bodyEn:
To: The Nodal Officer, Acquirer ({BENEFICIARY_BANK})
cc: The Concessionaire (MEP / IRB / etc.) at plaza {PLAZA_NAME}
cc: The Tag Issuer, {BANK_NAME}

Subject: Notice of negotiation-of-receipt — FASTag deduction Rs. {AMOUNT} (UTR {UTR}) at plaza {PLAZA_NAME} on {TXN_DATETIME} — Tag {TAG_ID} vehicle {VEHICLE_NO}

Sir / Madam,

1. I, {USER_NAME} (mobile {MOBILE_NO}), the registered holder of FASTag {TAG_ID} (vehicle {VEHICLE_NO}, RBI-issued insurance policy on file), hereby place on record that the deduction of Rs. {AMOUNT} (UTR {UTR}) made at your plaza {PLAZA_NAME} on {TXN_DATETIME} was NOT matched by a vehicle-side receipt, either at the lane-entry barrier or at the lane-exit barrier.

2. The standard prescribed under NPCI's 'Standards for FASTag Acquirer Reconciliation' (issue 4, January 2023) read with IHMCL SOP § 6.1 requires the acquirer to:
   (i) reconcile every deduction with an ANPR / lane-camera record of *physical crossing*; and
   (ii) bear the loss where such reconciliation is absent, without further proof on the customer side.

3. I have requested reconciliation in writing three times — on {COMPLAINT_DATE} (ref {TICKET_NO}), on {LAST_FOLLOWUP_DATE}, and via the issuer {BANK_NAME}'s grievance cell on the third occasion. The acquirer has not produced any reconciliation evidence. Under NPCI Standard 4 the deeming reversal applies.

4. I am willing to negotiate a non-reversal only against a complete and signed reconciliation pack duly transmitted by the Concessionaire to the issuer, within {DAYS_ELAPSED} days.

5. Failing the above, my next step will be a Section 35-A complaint to the Reserve Bank of India and an FIR under the Indian Penal Code Section 415/420 read with the Information Technology Act § 66-D.

Annexures: (i) Tag statement; (ii) my written reminders; (iii) issuer's ticketing trail; (iv) plaza lane-camera footage (only on production by the acquirer).

Place: {PLACE}
Date: {TODAY_DATE}

Yours faithfully,
{USER_NAME}
